# understand-anything scratch — only the working dirs are regenerable junk.
# The durable artifacts stay TRACKED: knowledge-graph.json, domain-graph.json,
# meta.json, config.json, .understandignore, and fingerprints.json.
# fingerprints.json is committed on purpose (plain file, no Git-LFS): with
# autoUpdate=true the plugin's hooks need a shared structural baseline, else a
# fresh clone treats every changed file as STRUCTURAL on its first incremental.
intermediate/
tmp/
.trash-*/
